[Influenza vaccination in the elderly population in Mexico: economic 
considerations].

[Article in Spanish]

Gutiérrez JP(1), Bertozzi SM.

Author information:
(1)División de Economía y Políticas de la Salud, Centro de Investigación en 
Sistemas de Salud, Instituto Nacional de Salud Pública, Cuernavaca, Morelos, 
México. jpgutier@insp.mx

OBJECTIVE: To estimate costs and health outcomes that could be attained by an 
influenza vaccination program in adults 65 years of age and older in Mexico.
MATERIAL AND METHODS: Between June and October 2004, a model was constructed to 
estimate the number of life years lost due to influenza and the fraction that 
could be prevented by vaccination among adults 65 years of age and older. The 
