DISCUSSION: Influenza vaccination among the elderly in Mexico would result in 
savings per life year saved well below the Mexican gross domestic product (GDP) 
per capita, suggesting, even without examining alternative uses for these 
resources, that this is a cost effective intervention in Mexico and probably 
also in other middle-income developing countries.

